# Frontend build-time config (Vite). Copy to .env.local for local overrides.
#
# Leave UNSET for local dev (Vite proxies /api -> http://localhost:4000).
#
# In production you have two choices:
#  - OPTION A (recommended): proxy /api via Netlify (see netlify.toml) and keep this UNSET.
#  - OPTION B: call the backend directly. Set this to your Railway API base, e.g.
#      VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://your-app.up.railway.app/api
#    and set CLIENT_ORIGIN on Railway to your Netlify URL (for CORS).
# VITE_API_BASE_URL=
